Simple staging for dotfiles
===========================

  1. Clone in the dot files for your favourite programmes.
  2. Convention:
     a) Adhere to a *-conf/ directory structure.
     b) Use a *-conf/install.sh file to instruct symlink locations.
  3. Run ./install

Git Submodules are encouraged and will be updated as part of the
`install` script.


Example usage
-------------

  % cd Source
  % git clone https://github.com/casr/dotfiles.git
  % cd dotfiles
  % git clone https://github.com/casr/dotfiles-vim.git vim-conf
  % git clone https://github.com/casr/dotfiles-zsh.git zsh-conf
  % ./install
  replace /Users/casr/.vim? y
  replace /Users/casr/.vimrc? y
  replace /Users/casr/.zshenv? n
  # Done.


Example install.sh
------------------

  LN=${LN:-ln -sh}              # Default link command

  BASEDIR=$(pwd)/$(dirname $0)  # Link to the right place
  BASEDIR=${BASEDIR#$HOME/}     # Saner links

  ${LN} $BASEDIR/vim   $HOME/.vim
  ${LN} $BASEDIR/vimrc $HOME/.vimrc
